description:
## Question:

Would it be a UX/UI improvement to only show the Environments Stopped tab if there is at least one stopped environment, and remove the tab from the UI if there are no stopped Environments?

## Current:

Under **Environments**, we always show the `Available` and `Stopped` tabs.  The `Stopped` tab has no stopped environments, and displays a page with a message that we have _no_ environments. 

![available-stopped](/uploads/84f881e64963bfccb26205903d3e697b/available-stopped.png)

![image](/uploads/ca3d474aaef8d04588348918c4a40c64/image.png)

## Proposal

What it looks like with the `Stopped` tab removed if there are no stopped environments:

![no-stopped](/uploads/762ce91c1bc28d2689d39ef8cf64179a/stopped.png)


## Code

The code to make this change would be pretty simple. In `app/assets/javascripts/environments/mixins/environments_mixin.js` we can change our `tabs` method to check if the stopped count is greater than zero.

```js
    tabs() {
      const tabsArray = [
        {
          name: s__('Available'),
          scope: 'available',
          count: this.state.availableCounter,
          isActive: this.scope === 'available',
        },
      ];

      if (this.state.stoppedCounter > 0) {
        tabsArray.push({
          name: s__('Stopped'),
          scope: 'stopped',
          count: this.state.stoppedCounter,
          isActive: this.scope === 'stopped',
        });
      }

      return tabsArray;
    },
```
